            "label": "Description of Programmatic Request (maximum of 150 words)\nIf this is a bill or report language request, enter \"N/A\"",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "We respectfully request $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD). This funding supports critical research across Earth Science, Planetary Science, Astrophysics, and Heliophysics. In FL-10, this investment directly benefits institutions like the University of Central Florida, which received over $57 million in recent NASA grants for pioneering work on lunar volcanism, planetary defense via radar characterization of hazardous asteroids, and exoplanet research. Sustaining this funding is essential to maintain U.S. leadership in space, counter international competition from China, and ensure the stability of a highly skilled aerospace workforce. Space science provides a 3:1 economic return, driving innovation that benefits all 50 states while inspiring the next generation of STEM professionals. This request aligns with the National Academies' Decadal Surveys, providing a rigorous, peer-reviewed basis for investment in our nation's most transformative scientific discoveries.",
            "rationale": "Description highlights the $9B request, specific local impact at UCF (lunar and asteroid research), and strategic arguments regarding workforce and international competition.",
